# MOC - From Asking for Answers to Applying Pressure

## The Three Shifts
- [[from-answers-to-pressure]] - the core shift: from asking for answers to asking for pressure
- [[tolerance-for-uncertainty]] - comfort with unfinished ideas, less compulsion to resolve
- [[scepticism-of-external-ideas]] - AI's unreliability trained broader critical thinking

## What It Produces
- [[positions-not-explanations]] - clearer positions rather than clearer explanations
- [[authorship-lives-in-judgement]] - confidence from the thinking, not the output
- [[ai-makes-thinking-harder-not-easier]] - more demanding, not less

## The Practices
- [[firewall-your-thinking]] - physically separate own ideas from external inputs
- [[ai-outputs-are-inputs]] - treat AI output as raw material, not truth
- [[deliberate-incompleteness]] - leave ideas unfinished as a deliberate holding state

